OL,3,CResident blames council inaction for
OL,4,Croad race crash
OL,6,FHe said a dike which funnels rainwater
OL,7,Finto underground pipes is not fit for
OL,8,Fpurpose, and has not been addressed
OL,9,Fdespite his complaints in recent
OL,10,Fmonths.JMr Stephenson said: "The
OL,11,Fcouncil aren't interested. They can't
OL,12,Fjust turn a blind eye to it. We all
OL,13,Fpay our taxes, we expect to get things
OL,14,Flike this done, especially when
OL,15,Fthere's no street lighting."JEast
OL,16,FRiding Council said it had been trying
OL,17,Fto fix the issue.JA spokesperson said:
OL,18,F"Despite the drainage being privately
OL,19,Fowned, the council recently carried
OL,20,Fout improvement works... The council
OL,21,Fintends to carry out further drainage
OL,22,Fworks to improve this situation even
OL,23,Fmore."JRace organisers have agreed to
OL,24,Frepair the damaged wall but insist the
OL,25,Fevent was a success ` and was safe.
OL,26,FMark Edwards, of Beverley and District
